Metro police assist the family following the home invasion. Photo: Kalisha Naicker Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - SA Community Crime Watch received a call from one of their members on their combined services WhatsApp group on Saturday January 14 requesting help after a intruder was discovered on their property in Key Ridge Road Shongweni.According to SACCW founder Steven King, the suspect then attacked the owner of the property and a scuffle ensued.&ldquo;The suspect had a knife and tried to stab the owner. His wife tried to assist by hitting the suspect with her paintball gun as their little boy stood by helpless,&rdquo; he said.The man eventually fled.However, within minutes of the call coming through to SACCW, SAPS Hillcrest, Shongweni K9, ER24, PMB Flying Squad, Drummond Farm Watch, Careline Crisis &amp; Trauma Centre and Metro K9 was mobilised to the area. A search took place for the beaten suspect, but he is still at large.The owner of the property was taken for a checkup and the family received counselling. King thanked the role players for the response and wished the family a speedy recovery.&ldquo;Without such a speedy response the ordeal could have ended in tragedy.&rdquo;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.